Shearlink Capital Has Raised Bright Horizons Fam Sol In D (BFAM) Stake; Compass Group Diversified Holdings (CODI)’s Sentiment Is 1.92


					
						July 24, 2017 - By Peter Erickson

Shearlink Capital Llc increased Bright Horizons Fam Sol In D (BFAM) stake by 25.96% reported in 2016Q4 SEC filing. Shearlink Capital Llc acquired 42,422 shares as Bright Horizons Fam Sol In D (BFAM)’s stock rose 9.89%. The Shearlink Capital Llc holds 205,806 shares with $14.41 million value, up from 163,384 last quarter. Bright Horizons Fam Sol In D now has $4.77B valuation. The stock rose 0.38% or $0.31 reaching $79.83 per share. About 89,033 shares traded. Bright Horizons Family Solutions Inc (NYSE:BFAM) has risen 18.19% since July 24, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 1.49% the S&P500.







Compass Diversified Holdings and Compass Group Diversified Holdings, LLC, (the Company), acquires and manages small and middle-market businesses. The company has market cap of $1.04 billion. The Firm operates through divisions include Acquisition Corp. (5.11 Tactical), The Ergo Baby Carrier, Inc. (Ergobaby), Liberty Safe and Security Products, Inc. (Liberty), Fresh Hemp Foods Ltd. (Manitoba Harvest), Compass AC Holdings, Inc. (ACI), AMT Acquisition Corporation (Arnold), Clean Earth Holdings, Inc. (Clean Earth), and Sterno Products, LLC (Sterno) divisions. It has a 107.93 P/E ratio. The Firm categorizes the businesses into separate groups of businesses, such as branded consumer businesses and niche industrial businesses.
 About 86,911 shares traded. Compass Diversified Holdings (CODI) has risen 3.37% since July 24, 2016 and is uptrending. It has underperformed by 13.33% the S&P500.
Analysts await Compass Diversified Holdings (NYSE:CODI) to report earnings on August, 2. They expect $0.37 earnings per share, up 12.12% or $0.04 from last year’s $0.33 per share. CODI’s profit will be $22.11M for 11.76 P/E if the $0.37 EPS becomes a reality. After $-0.29 actual earnings per share reported by Compass Diversified Holdings for the previous quarter, Wall Street now forecasts -227.59% EPS growth. 
Essex Financial Services Inc. holds 2.18% of its portfolio in Compass Diversified Holdings for 567,826 shares. Gilman Hill Asset Management Llc owns 268,066 shares or 1.77% of their US portfolio. Moreover, Investment Counselors Of Maryland Llc has 1.01% invested in the company for 1.07 million shares. The New York-based Wellington Shields & Co. Llc has invested 0.46% in the stock. Yorktown Management & Research Co Inc, a Virginia-based fund reported 100,000 shares.
Investors sentiment increased to 1.16 in Q4 2016. Its up 0.28, from 0.88 in 2016Q3. It improved, as 12 investors sold BFAM shares while 73 reduced holdings. 31 funds opened positions while 68 raised stakes. 57.43 million shares or 1.24% less from 58.16 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported. Blackrock Institutional Trust Na holds 0.01% of its portfolio in Bright Horizons Family Solutions Inc (NYSE:BFAM) for 1.27 million shares. Sei Company holds 0.05% or 151,488 shares in its portfolio. Glenmede Trust Na reported 0% of its portfolio in Bright Horizons Family Solutions Inc (NYSE:BFAM). Timessquare Mgmt Ltd Limited Liability Company reported 1.16% of its portfolio in Bright Horizons Family Solutions Inc (NYSE:BFAM). Massmutual Fsb Adv owns 15,440 shares or 0% of their US portfolio. Tygh Inc holds 57,197 shares. First Tru Advsr Lp holds 0.01% or 44,919 shares. Next Group Inc holds 0% or 65 shares in its portfolio. Barclays Pcl holds 0.02% or 290,947 shares in its portfolio. Jpmorgan Chase And has 75,110 shares. Invesco Limited has 0.01% invested in Bright Horizons Family Solutions Inc (NYSE:BFAM) for 220,723 shares. Sawgrass Asset Mngmt Ltd accumulated 7,830 shares. Barrett Asset Ltd Limited Liability Company owns 1,700 shares or 0.01% of their US portfolio. Ironbridge Mngmt Lp has 0.22% invested in Bright Horizons Family Solutions Inc (NYSE:BFAM). Stephens Mngmt Group Lc owns 320,619 shares.
Among 7 analysts covering Bright Horizons (NYSE:BFAM), 4 have Buy rating, 0 Sell and 3 Hold. Therefore 57% are positive. Bright Horizons had 13 analyst reports since August 5, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. RBC Capital Markets maintained Bright Horizons Family Solutions Inc (NYSE:BFAM) on Wednesday, August 5 with “Outperform” rating. The rating was reinitiated by Credit Suisse with “Outperform” on Wednesday, February 3. The firm earned “Market Weight” rating on Wednesday, November 2 by William Blair. The firm has “Outperform” rating by RBC Capital Markets given on Monday, November 9. William Blair downgraded the shares of BFAM in report on Friday, February 10 to “Market Perform” rating. As per Tuesday, February 9, the company rating was maintained by RBC Capital Markets. Credit Suisse downgraded the shares of BFAM in report on Friday, May 12 to “Neutral” rating. The firm has “Overweight” rating by Barclays Capital given on Wednesday, November 25. The firm has “Overweight” rating by JP Morgan given on Monday, August 15.








By Peter Erickson
